  "prompt": "Which app should I use to locate lost or stolen phone even after a factory reset is performed? My phone is rooted.",
  "response": "If your phone is rooted, you have several options to locate it even if a factory reset has been performed:\n\n1. **Cerberus**: This app offers multiple features for locating and controlling your phone remotely. It can survive a factory reset if it is installed as a system app (which requires root access). You can track your phone, take pictures, record audio, and more.\n\n2. **Prey Anti Theft**: Prey also provides tracking and control features. It can survive a factory reset if properly configured with root access.\n\n3. **Find My Device**: Though typically, this Google service does not survive a factory reset, if rooted, there might be ways to make it harder to remove. However, its main advantage is that it is integrated into Android's default set of services.\n\n4. **Offline GPS Tracker (similar apps)**: Some rooted-specific tracker apps can survive a reset and still provide location information after a reset.\n\nIt\u2019s important to ensure that any anti-theft app is installed properly with root privileges and configured to survive a factory reset. Always check the app's documentation and community forums for specific instructions related to rooted devices. Proper configuration is key to ensuring these apps work correctly after a factory reset.",
